Do you need to sell the domain model then? It's just an implementation detail that lets you Avoid Risks with using a "raw" LLM.

I'd just say; 
&gt; we can't risk using an LLM at the moment because how it thinks is a black box. When it learns it develops "concepts" of some sort, but we can't know if these internally categories are, for example, illegally racist. We need to develop a shared intermediary language that both the LLM and technical users can read and understand. This will let us check and control the LLM's thinking
